Create a pending proposal for a new calendar event. Pass a `draft` with `summary`, `start_at`, `end_at`, optional `timezone`, optional `description` and `location`, and any attendees. If `timezone` is omitted, Spacebot defaults it to the agent/user timezone; do not silently convert local user times to UTC unless the user explicitly asked for UTC. This does not write to the remote calendar yet; it returns a proposal. If the user has already clearly asked for this exact event to be created, follow up with `calendar_apply` in the same branch.
